
get_metadata_scholarly.py uses a python library to get metadata on papers 
from Google Scholar based on title. This might help extract the venue
from a string citation.

fuzzymatch.py maps venues to DBLP-indexed venues. It will normalize the
venue titles for grouping etc. When there isn't an exact match, it does
fuzzy matching.

dblp-labels.csv is a list of all DBLP-indexed venues with the title used
in the DBLP database.

mega-spreadsheet-clean.csv is just so it's easy to see what the input
looked like for fuzzy.
